- What's a Wrackspurt?
- They're invisible creatures.

238
00:22:54,037 --> 00:22:57,748
They float in your ears
and make your brain go fuzzy.

239
00:22:57,749 --> 00:22:58,361
<i>Quibbler.</i>

240
00:23:09,761 --> 00:23:12,680
RON: So, what was Draco doing
with that Weird-looking Cabinet?

241
00:23:12,681 --> 00:23:14,557
And who were all those people?

242
00:23:14,558 --> 00:23:17,852
Don't you see?
It was a ceremony, an initiation.

243
00:23:17,853 --> 00:23:19,937
Stop it, Harry.
I know where you're going.

244
00:23:19,938 --> 00:23:22,606
It's happened. He's one of them.

245
00:23:22,607 --> 00:23:24,859
One of what?

246
00:23:24,860 --> 00:23:28,487
Harry is under the impression
Draco Malfoy is now a Death Eater.

247
00:23:28,488 --> 00:23:30,614
You're barking.

248
00:23:30,615 --> 00:23:32,908
What would You-Know-Who
want with Malfoy?

249
00:23:32,909 --> 00:23:37,121
Well, then what's he doing in
Borgin and Burkes? Browsing for furniture?

250
00:23:37,122 --> 00:23:39,164
It's a creepy shop. He's a creepy bloke.

251
00:23:39,165 --> 00:23:43,210
Look, his father is a Death Eater.
It only makes sense.

252
00:23:43,211 --> 00:23:44,962
Hermione saw it with her own eyes.

253
00:23:44,963 --> 00:23:49,963
I told you, I don't know what I saw.

254
00:23:50,010 --> 00:23:55,010
I need some air.

255
00:24:08,278 --> 00:24:13,278
MAN: Don't worry. When we get
to Hogwarts, we'll sort it out.

256
00:24:27,881 --> 00:24:32,468
[CHATTERING]

257
00:24:32,469 --> 00:24:35,888
DRACO: What was that? Blaise?
BLAISE: Don't know.

258
00:24:35,889 --> 00:24:39,183
PANSY: Relax, boys. It's probably just
a first-year messing around.

259
00:24:39,184 --> 00:24:44,184
Come on, Draco. Sit down.
We'll be at Hogwarts soon.

260
00:24:52,238 --> 00:24:56,200
Hogwarts.
What a pathetic excuse for a school.

261
00:24:56,201 --> 00:24:58,369
I'd pitch myself off
the Astronomy Tower...

262
00:24:58,370 --> 00:25:00,663
if I had to continue
for another two years.

263
00:25:00,664 --> 00:25:03,248
What's that supposed to mean?

264
00:25:03,249 --> 00:25:07,252
Let's just say I don't think you'll see me
wasting my time in Charms class next year.

265
00:25:07,253 --> 00:25:08,879
[BLAISE LAUGHS]

266
00:25:08,880 --> 00:25:12,174
Amused, Blaise?

267
00:25:12,175 --> 00:25:17,175
We'll see just Who's laughing in the end.

268
00:25:36,741 --> 00:25:41,741
You two go on.
I wanna check something.

269
00:25:42,664 --> 00:25:44,123
Where's Harry?

270
00:25:44,124 --> 00:25:49,124
He's probably already on the platform.
Come on.

271
00:26:02,767 --> 00:26:06,437
DRACO: Didn't Mummy ever tell you
it was rude to eavesdrop, Potter?

272
00:26:06,438 --> 00:26:11,438
<i>Petrificus Tota/us.</i>

273
00:26:19,242 --> 00:26:21,118
Oh, yeah...

274
00:26:21,119 --> 00:26:26,119
she was dead before you could wipe
the drool off your chin.

275
00:26:29,919 --> 00:26:34,919
That's for my father.
Enjoy your ride back to London.

276
00:27:16,925 --> 00:27:17,425
<i>Finite.</i>

277
00:27:24,808 --> 00:27:26,475
- Hello, Harry.
- Luna!

278
00:27:26,476 --> 00:27:31,476
- How'd you know where I was?
- Wrackspurts. Your head's full of them.

279
00:27:37,904 --> 00:27:40,739
HARRY: Sorry I made you miss
the carriages, by the way, Luna.

280
00:27:40,740 --> 00:27:44,076
LUNA: That's all right.
It was like being with a friend.

281
00:27:44,077 --> 00:27:46,537
Oh, I am your friend, Luna.

282
00:27:46,538 --> 00:27:48,497
That's nice.

283
00:27:48,498 --> 00:27:51,875
About time. I've been looking
all over for you two.

284
00:27:51,876 --> 00:27:54,962
Right. Names?

285
00:27:54,963 --> 00:27:57,506
Professor Flitwick,
you've known me for five years.

286
00:27:57,507 --> 00:28:00,175
No exceptions, Potter.

287
00:28:00,176 --> 00:28:02,094
Who are those people?

288
00:28:02,095 --> 00:28:04,555
Aurors. For security.

289
00:28:04,556 --> 00:28:06,306
What's this Cane here, then?

290
00:28:06,307 --> 00:28:08,725
DRACO: It's not a Cane, you cretin.
It's a walking stick.

291
00:28:08,726 --> 00:28:13,726
FILCH: And what exactly would you
be wanting with a...?

292
00:28:13,898 --> 00:28:17,151
Could be construed
as an offensive weapon.

293
00:28:17,152 --> 00:28:22,152
It's all right, Mr. Filch.
I can vouch for Mr. Malfoy.

294
00:28:29,789 --> 00:28:34,789
DRACO: Nice face, Potter.

295
00:28:38,298 --> 00:28:40,799
Would you like me to fix it for you?

296
00:28:40,800 --> 00:28:44,761
Personally, I think you look
a bit more devil-may-care this way...

297
00:28:44,762 --> 00:28:46,722
but it's up to you.

298
00:28:46,723 --> 00:28:49,183
Well, have you ever fixed a nose before?

299
00:28:49,184 --> 00:28:53,937
No, but I've done several toes,
and how different are they, really?

300
00:28:53,938 --> 00:28:58,938
Um... Okay, yeah. Give it a go.

301
00:29:00,278 --> 00:29:02,487
<i>'Episkey_ - Ahl</i>

302
00:29:02,488 --> 00:29:07,488
[HARRY GROANING]

303
00:29:08,453 --> 00:29:12,748
- How do I look?
- Exceptionally ordinary.

304
00:29:12,749 --> 00:29:16,960
Brilliant.

305
00:29:16,961 --> 00:29:21,506
[CHATTERING]

306
00:29:21,507 --> 00:29:26,507
RON:
Don't worry. He'll be here in a minute.

307
00:29:27,430 --> 00:29:30,307
Will you stop eating?

308
00:29:30,308 --> 00:29:32,726
Your best friend is missing!

309
00:29:32,727 --> 00:29:37,727
Di. Turn around, you lunatic.

310
00:29:38,775 --> 00:29:40,901
GINNY:
He's covered in blood again.

311
00:29:40,902 --> 00:29:45,155
- Why is it he's always covered in blood?
- Looks like it's his own this time.

312
00:29:45,156 --> 00:29:47,199
Where have you been?

313
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:49,826
- What happened to your face?
- Later.

314
00:29:49,827 --> 00:29:51,995
What've I missed?

315
00:29:51,996 --> 00:29:55,958
Sorting Hat urged us all to be brave
and strong in these troubled times.

316
00:29:55,959 --> 00:30:00,959
Easy for it to say, huh?
It's a hat, isn't it?

317
00:30:07,345 --> 00:30:09,221
DUMBLEDORE:
Very best of evenings to you all.

318
00:30:09,222 --> 00:30:12,474
HARRY: Thanks.

319
00:30:12,475 --> 00:30:17,312
First off, let me introduce
the newest member of our staff...

320
00:30:17,313 --> 00:30:19,731
Horace Slughorn.

321
00:30:19,732 --> 00:30:23,443
[STUDENTS APPLAUDING]

322
00:30:23,444 --> 00:30:25,487
Professor Slughorn, I'm happy to say...

323
00:30:25,488 --> 00:30:29,950
has agreed to resume
his old post as Potions Master.

324
00:30:29,951 --> 00:30:33,036
Meanwhile, the post of
Defense Against the Dark Arts...

325
00:30:33,037 --> 00:30:35,247
will be taken by Professor Snape.

326
00:30:35,248 --> 00:30:36,873
STUDENTS: Snape?

327
00:30:36,874 --> 00:30:41,874
[STUDENTS CLAPPING]

328
00:30:42,755 --> 00:30:44,548
DUMBLEDORE: Now, as you know...

329
00:30:44,549 --> 00:30:48,385
each and every one of you was searched
upon your arrival here tonight.

330
00:30:48,386 --> 00:30:51,179
And you have the right to know why.

331
00:30:51,180 --> 00:30:54,933
Cnce there was a young man,
who, like you...

332
00:30:54,934 --> 00:30:57,769
sat in this very hall...

333
00:30:57,770 --> 00:31:02,770
walked this castle's corridors,
slept under its roof.

334
00:31:02,984 --> 00:31:07,529
He seemed to all the world
a student like any other.

335
00:31:07,530 --> 00:31:10,532
His name?

336
00:31:10,533 --> 00:31:12,034
Tom Riddle.

337
00:31:12,035 --> 00:31:17,035
[MURMURING]

338
00:31:17,040 --> 00:31:19,249
Today, of course...

339
00:31:19,250 --> 00:31:23,754
he's known all over the world
by another name.

340
00:31:23,755 --> 00:31:28,755
Which is why, as I stand looking out
upon you all tonight...

341
00:31:29,135 --> 00:31:32,679
I'm reminded of a sobering fact.

342
00:31:32,680 --> 00:31:35,974
Every day, every hour...

343
00:31:35,975 --> 00:31:38,101
this very minute, perhaps...

344
00:31:38,102 --> 00:31:43,102
dark forces attempt to penetrate
this castle's walls.

345
00:31:44,067 --> 00:31:49,067
But in the end,
their greatest weapon is you.

346
00:31:52,658 --> 00:31:56,036
Just something to think about.

347
00:31:56,037 --> 00:31:59,289
Now, off to bed. Pip-pip.

348
00:31:59,290 --> 00:32:04,290
RON: That was cheerful.

349
00:32:06,381 --> 00:32:11,381
History of Magic is upstairs,
ladies, not down.

350
00:32:11,928 --> 00:32:16,928
Mr. Davies! Mr. Davies!
That is the girls' Iavatow.

351
00:32:19,727 --> 00:32:22,479
Potter.

352
00:32:22,480 --> 00:32:27,480
Oh, this can't be good.

353
00:32:27,735 --> 00:32:30,028
Enjoying ourselves, are we?

354
00:32:30,029 --> 00:32:33,740
- I had a free period this morning, professor.
- So I noticed.

355
00:32:33,741 --> 00:32:36,326
I would think you would want to
fill it with Potions.

356
00:32:36,327 --> 00:32:39,788
Or is it no longer your ambition
to become an Auror?

357
00:32:39,789 --> 00:32:43,583
It was, but I was told I had to
get an "Outstanding" in my O.W.L.

358
00:32:43,584 --> 00:32:46,628
So you did, when Professor Snape
was teaching Potions.

359
00:32:46,629 --> 00:32:51,383
However, Professor Slughorn is perfectly
happy to accept N.E.W.T.s students...

360
00:32:51,384 --> 00:32:53,677
with "Exceeds Expectations."

361
00:32:53,678 --> 00:32:55,512
Brilliant. Um...

362
00:32:55,513 --> 00:32:58,140
- Well, I'll head there straightaway.
- Oh, good, good.

363
00:32:58,141 --> 00:33:03,141
Potter, take Weasley with you.
He looks far too happy over there.

364
00:33:04,856 --> 00:33:06,314
RON:
I don't wanna take Potions.

365
00:33:06,315 --> 00:33:10,277
There's Quidditch trials coming up.
I need to practice.

366
00:33:10,278 --> 00:33:15,278
SLUGHORN: Attention to detail in the preparation
is the prerequisite of all planning.

367
00:33:16,200 --> 00:33:17,742
Ah.

368
00:33:17,743 --> 00:33:22,289
Harry, my boy, I was beginning to worry.
We've brought someone with us, I see.

369
00:33:22,290 --> 00:33:24,040
Ron Weasley, sir.

370
00:33:24,041 --> 00:33:26,668
But I'm dead awful at Potions,
a menace, actually.

371
00:33:26,669 --> 00:33:29,004
- I'm gonna...
SLUGHORN: Nonsense, we'll sort you out.

372
00:33:29,005 --> 00:33:32,174
Any friend of Harry's is a friend of mine.
Get your books out.

373
00:33:32,175 --> 00:33:34,885
HARRY: I haven't actually got
my book yet, and nor has Ron.

374
00:33:34,886 --> 00:33:36,761
Get what you want from the cupboard.

375
00:33:36,762 --> 00:33:40,265
Now, as I was saying,
I prepared some concoctions this morning.

376
00:33:40,266 --> 00:33:45,266
Any ideas what these might be?

377
00:33:45,730 --> 00:33:50,730
- Yes, Miss...?
- Granger, sir.

378
00:33:51,569 --> 00:33:56,198
That one there is Veritaserum.
It's a truth-telling serum.

379
00:33:56,199 --> 00:34:01,199
And that would be Polyjuice Potion.

380
00:34:02,538 --> 00:34:04,372
It's terribly tricky to make.

381
00:34:04,373 --> 00:34:06,583
And this is Amortentia...

382
00:34:06,584 --> 00:34:09,920
the most powerful
love potion in the world.

383
00:34:09,921 --> 00:34:14,921
It's rumored to smell differently to each
person according to what attracts them.

384
00:34:15,051 --> 00:34:17,802
For example, I smell...

385
00:34:17,803 --> 00:34:22,015
freshly mown grass,
and new parchment, and...

386
00:34:22,016 --> 00:34:26,770
spearmint toothpaste.

387
00:34:26,771 --> 00:34:30,398
SLUGHORN: Now, Amortentia doesn't create
actual love. That would be impossible.

388
00:34:30,399 --> 00:34:35,399
But it does cause
a powerful infatuation or obsession.

389
00:34:35,571 --> 00:34:40,571
And for that reason, it is probably
the most dangerous potion in this room.

390
00:34:47,792 --> 00:34:50,961
Sir? You haven't told us
what's in that one.

391
00:34:50,962 --> 00:34:52,837
Oh, yes.

392
00:34:52,838 --> 00:34:55,590
What you see before you,
ladies and gentlemen...

393
00:34:55,591 --> 00:35:00,591
is a curious little potion
known as Felix Felicis.

394
00:35:01,430 --> 00:35:03,848
But it is more commonly referred to as...

395
00:35:03,849 --> 00:35:08,849
- Liquid luck.
- Yes, Miss Granger. Liquid luck.

396
00:35:09,647 --> 00:35:13,441
Desperately tricky to make,
disastrous should you get it wrong.

397
00:35:13,442 --> 00:35:18,442
One sip and you will find
that all of your endeavors succeed.

398
00:35:20,491 --> 00:35:23,827
At least until the effects wear off.

399
00:35:23,828 --> 00:35:27,831
So this is what I offer each of you today.

400
00:35:27,832 --> 00:35:32,832
One tiny vial of liquid luck to the student
who, in the hour that remains...

401
00:35:32,837 --> 00:35:37,591
manages to brew an acceptable
Draught of Living Death...

402
00:35:37,592 --> 00:35:41,011
the recipes for which can be found
on page 10 of your books.

403
00:35:41,012 --> 00:35:44,848
I should point out, however, only once did
a student manage to brew a potion...

404
00:35:44,849 --> 00:35:48,852
of sufficient quality
to claim this prize.

405
00:35:48,853 --> 00:35:51,896
Nevertheless, good luck to you all.

406
00:35:51,897 --> 00:35:56,897
Let the brewing commence.

407
00:36:29,518 --> 00:36:31,895
How did you do that?

408
00:36:31,896 --> 00:36:34,230
You crush it. Don't cut it.

409
00:36:34,231 --> 00:36:36,900
No. The instructions
specifically say to cut.

410
00:36:36,901 --> 00:36:41,901
No, really.

411
00:37:16,232 --> 00:37:20,902
Merlin's beard! It is perfect.

412
00:37:20,903 --> 00:37:25,903
So perfect I daresay
one drop would kill us all.

413
00:37:27,410 --> 00:37:29,536
So here we are, then, as promised.

414
00:37:29,537 --> 00:37:32,914
One vial of Felix Felicis.

415
00:37:32,915 --> 00:37:35,458
Congratulations.

416
00:37:35,459 --> 00:37:40,459
Use it well.

417
00:37:58,649 --> 00:38:03,649
[KNOCKING]

418
00:38:05,823 --> 00:38:10,160
DUMBLEDORE:
Harry, you got my message. Come in.

419
00:38:10,161 --> 00:38:11,703
How are you?

420
00:38:11,704 --> 00:38:13,413
I'm fine, sir.

421
00:38:13,414 --> 00:38:15,915
Enjoying your classes?

422
00:38:15,916 --> 00:38:19,669
I know Professor Slughorn
is most impressed with you.

423
00:38:19,670 --> 00:38:22,672
I think he overestimates my abilities, sir.

424
00:38:22,673 --> 00:38:24,340
Do you?

425
00:38:24,341 --> 00:38:25,759
Definitely.

426
00:38:25,760 --> 00:38:27,594
[DUMBLEDORE CHUCKLES]

427
00:38:27,595 --> 00:38:31,639
What about your activities
outside the classroom?

428
00:38:31,640 --> 00:38:33,808
- Sir?
- Well, I notice you spend...

429
00:38:33,809 --> 00:38:36,603
a great deal of time with Miss Granger.

430
00:38:36,604 --> 00:38:38,021
I can't help wondering...

431
00:38:38,022 --> 00:38:43,022
Oh, no, no. I mean, she's brilliant,
and we're friends, but, no.

432
00:38:43,194 --> 00:38:47,280
Forgive me. I was merely being curious.

433
00:38:47,281 --> 00:38:49,365
But enough chitchat.

434
00:38:49,366 --> 00:38:53,536
You must be wondering
why I summoned you here tonight.

435
00:38:53,537 --> 00:38:57,373
The answer lies here.

436
00:38:57,374 --> 00:38:59,709
What you are looking at are memories.

437
00:38:59,710 --> 00:39:03,713
In this case,
pertaining to one individual, Voldemort...

438
00:39:03,714 --> 00:39:08,714
or, as he was known then, Tom Riddle.

439
00:39:09,220 --> 00:39:13,223
This vial contains
the most particular memory...

440
00:39:13,224 --> 00:39:16,768
of the day I first met him.

441
00:39:16,769 --> 00:39:21,769
I'd like you to see it, if you would.

442
00:39:57,184 --> 00:40:01,771
WOMAN: <i>I admit some confusion
upon receiving your letter, Mr. Dumbledore.</i>

443
00:40:01,772 --> 00:40:05,400
In all the years Tom's been here,
he's never once had a family visitor.

444
00:40:05,401 --> 00:40:10,401
There have been incidents
with the other children. Nasty things.

445
00:40:11,574 --> 00:40:14,284
Tom, you have a visitor.

446
00:40:14,285 --> 00:40:19,285
How do you do, Tom?

447
00:40:23,460 --> 00:40:23,960
Don't.

448
00:40:32,511 --> 00:40:35,805
- You're the doctor, aren't you?
- No.

449
00:40:35,806 --> 00:40:38,558
I am a professor.

450
00:40:38,559 --> 00:40:40,560
I don't believe you.

451
00:40:40,561 --> 00:40:43,146
She wants me looked at.

452
00:40:43,147 --> 00:40:45,523
They think I'm different.

453
00:40:45,524 --> 00:40:47,191
Well, perhaps they're right.

454
00:40:47,192 --> 00:40:48,818
I'm not mad.

455
00:40:48,819 --> 00:40:52,322
Hogwarts is not a place for mad people.

456
00:40:52,323 --> 00:40:55,074
Hogwarts is a school.

457
00:40:55,075 --> 00:41:00,075
A school of magic.

458
00:41:00,748 --> 00:41:04,626
You can do things, can't you, Tom?

459
00:41:04,627 --> 00:41:08,671
Things other children can't.

460
00:41:08,672 --> 00:41:12,550
I can make things move
without touching them.

461
00:41:12,551 --> 00:41:16,930
I can make animals do what I want
without training them.

462
00:41:16,931 --> 00:41:21,100
I can make bad things happen
to people who are mean to me.

463
00:41:21,101 --> 00:41:23,686
I can make them hurt...

464
00:41:23,687 --> 00:41:25,772
if I want.

465
00:41:25,773 --> 00:41:27,815
Who are you?

466
00:41:27,816 --> 00:41:31,194
Well, I'm like you, Tom.

467
00:41:31,195 --> 00:41:33,696
I'm different.

468
00:41:33,697 --> 00:41:34,309
Prove it.

469
00:41:42,706 --> 00:41:47,706
I think there's something in your wardrobe
trying to get out, Tom.

470
00:41:56,261 --> 00:42:00,223
Thievery is not tolerated at Hogwarts,
Tom.

471
00:42:00,224 --> 00:42:05,224
At Hogwarts, you'll be taught not only
how to use magic, but how to control it.

472
00:42:06,063 --> 00:42:11,063
You understand me?

473
00:42:11,193 --> 00:42:14,988
I can speak to snakes too.

474
00:42:14,989 --> 00:42:17,782
They find me.

475
00:42:17,783 --> 00:42:19,951
Whisper things.

476
00:42:19,952 --> 00:42:24,952
Is that normal for someone like me?

477
00:42:44,143 --> 00:42:47,603
Did you know, sir? Then?

478
00:42:47,604 --> 00:42:52,604
Did I know I'd just met the most
dangerous dark wizard of all time? No.

479
00:42:53,819 --> 00:42:57,572
If I had, I...

480
00:42:57,573 --> 00:43:00,199
Over time, while here at Hogwarts...

481
00:43:00,200 --> 00:43:03,703
Tom Riddle grew close
to one particular teacher.

482
00:43:03,704 --> 00:43:08,458
Can you guess
who that teacher might be?

483
00:43:08,459 --> 00:43:12,086
You didn't bring Professor Slughorn back
simply to teach Potions, did you?

484
00:43:12,087 --> 00:43:14,297
No, I did not.

485
00:43:14,298 --> 00:43:19,135
You see, Professor Slughorn possesses
something I desire very dearly.

486
00:43:19,136 --> 00:43:21,179
And he will not give it up easily.

487
00:43:21,180 --> 00:43:24,557
You said Professor Slughorn
would try to collect me.

488
00:43:24,558 --> 00:43:26,517
I did.

489
00:43:26,518 --> 00:43:29,896
Do you want me to let him?

490
00:43:29,897 --> 00:43:30,397
Yes.

491
00:44:07,059 --> 00:44:12,059
[RECORD SKIPPING]

492
00:44:51,603 --> 00:44:55,439
[CHATTERING]

493
00:44:55,440 --> 00:44:57,316
HARRY: All right. Um...

494
00:44:57,317 --> 00:45:00,570
This morning, I'm gonna be
putting you all through a few drills...

495
00:45:00,571 --> 00:45:03,406
just to assess your strengths.

496
00:45:03,407 --> 00:45:05,575
Quiet! Please!

497
00:45:05,576 --> 00:45:06,909
Shut it!

498
00:45:06,910 --> 00:45:10,580
[CHATTERING STOPS]

499
00:45:10,581 --> 00:45:13,499
Thanks. All right. Um...

500
00:45:13,500 --> 00:45:15,793
Just because you
made the team last year...

501
00:45:15,794 --> 00:45:20,794
does not guarantee you a spot this year.
Is that clear?

502
00:45:21,258 --> 00:45:24,343
Good.

503
00:45:24,344 --> 00:45:29,344
[FLY BUZZING]

504
00:45:31,268 --> 00:45:34,020
No hard feelings, Weasley, all right?

505
00:45:34,021 --> 00:45:35,396
Hard feelings?

506
00:45:35,397 --> 00:45:39,108
Yeah, I'll be going out for Keeper as well.
It's nothing personal.

507
00:45:39,109 --> 00:45:41,944
Really? Strapping guy like you?

508
00:45:41,945 --> 00:45:44,697
You've got more of a Beater's build,
don't you think?

509
00:45:44,698 --> 00:45:47,283
Keepers need to be quick, agile.

510
00:45:47,284 --> 00:45:48,492
[BUZZING STOPS]

511
00:45:48,493 --> 00:45:50,453
Oh, I like my chances.

512
00:45:50,454 --> 00:45:54,415
Say, think you could introduce me
to your friend Granger?

513
00:45:54,416 --> 00:45:59,416
Wouldn't mind getting on
a first-name basis, know what I mean?

514
00:46:10,891 --> 00:46:12,767
MAN 1: Come on, Weasley!

515
00:46:12,768 --> 00:46:16,020
WOMAN: Come on, Ron!
MAN 2: Go on, Weasley!

516
00:46:16,021 --> 00:46:19,065
MAN 3: Go on, Weasley!
MAN 4: Yeah, Ron!

517
00:46:19,066 --> 00:46:24,066
MAN 5: Go on, Cormac!

518
00:46:25,989 --> 00:46:30,989
[GRUNTING]

519
00:46:36,833 --> 00:46:41,833
WOMAN: Come on, Ron!

520
00:46:47,219 --> 00:46:49,595
MAN 6: Come on, Ron.

521
00:46:49,596 --> 00:46:54,596
Come on, Ron.

522
00:47:09,366 --> 00:47:14,366
<i>Confundus.</i>

523
00:47:26,633 --> 00:47:31,633
Isn't he brilliant?

524
00:47:31,722 --> 00:47:35,558
I have to admit, I thought
I was gonna miss that last one.

525
00:47:35,559 --> 00:47:38,769
I hope Cormac's not taking it too hard.

526
00:47:38,770 --> 00:47:42,898
He's got a bit of a thing for you,
Hermione. Cormac.

527
00:47:42,899 --> 00:47:47,899
He's vile.

528
00:47:49,865 --> 00:47:52,283
HARRY: Have you ever heard of this spell?
Sectumsempra?

529
00:47:52,284 --> 00:47:54,535
No, I haven't.

530
00:47:54,536 --> 00:47:57,830
And if you had a shred of self-respect,
you'd hand that book in.

531
00:47:57,831 --> 00:48:00,458
Not bloody likely. He's top of the class.

532
00:48:00,459 --> 00:48:05,459
He's even better than you, Hermione.
Slughorn thinks he's a genius.

533
00:48:05,756 --> 00:48:07,882
What?

534
00:48:07,883 --> 00:48:10,760
I'd like to know whose that book was.
Let's have a look.

535
00:48:10,761 --> 00:48:13,763
No.

536
00:48:13,764 --> 00:48:15,598
HERMIONE: Why not?

537
00:48:15,599 --> 00:48:17,391
The binding is fragile.

538
00:48:17,392 --> 00:48:22,392
HERMIONE: The binding is fragile?
- Yeah.

539
00:48:24,274 --> 00:48:26,025
- Who's the Half-Blood Prince?
- Who?

540
00:48:26,026 --> 00:48:31,026
That's what it says right here: "This book
is property of the Half-Blood Prince."

541
00:48:47,130 --> 00:48:50,633
<i>HERMIONE: For weeks you carry around
this book, practically sleep with</i> it...

542
00:48:50,634 --> 00:48:53,094
<i>yet you have no desire to find out
who he is?</i>

543
00:48:53,095 --> 00:48:56,680
HARRY: L didn't say I wasn't curious,
and I don't sleep with it.

544
00:48:56,681 --> 00:48:57,890
RON: Well, it's true.

545
00:48:57,891 --> 00:49:01,811
I like a nice chat before I go to bed.
Now all you do is read that bloody book.

546
00:49:01,812 --> 00:49:05,106
It's just like being with Hermione.

547
00:49:05,107 --> 00:49:07,775
HERMIONE:
Well, I was curious, so I went to...

548
00:49:07,776 --> 00:49:11,237
- The library.
- The library. And?

549
00:49:11,238 --> 00:49:13,030
And nothing.

550
00:49:13,031 --> 00:49:16,200
I couldn't find a reference anywhere
to a Half-Blood Prince.

551
00:49:16,201 --> 00:49:18,494
- There we go. That settles it, then.
SLUGHORN: Filius!

552
00:49:18,495 --> 00:49:20,996
I was hoping to find you
in the Three Broomsticks!

553
00:49:20,997 --> 00:49:25,997
No, emergency choir practice,
I'm afraid, Horace.

554
00:49:29,172 --> 00:49:31,841
Does anyone fancy a Butterbeer?

555
00:49:31,842 --> 00:49:34,343
A chum of mine
was sledging down Claxby Hill.

556
00:49:34,344 --> 00:49:38,139
We had a very long, homemade,
Norwegian-style sledge...

557
00:49:38,140 --> 00:49:41,225
HARRY:
No, not there. Over here.

558
00:49:41,226 --> 00:49:44,520
No, sit beside me.

559
00:49:44,521 --> 00:49:47,273
Okay.

560
00:49:47,274 --> 00:49:48,816
MAN: Something to drink?

561
00:49:48,817 --> 00:49:53,817
HERMIONE: Three Butterbeers,
and some ginger in mine, please.

562
00:49:57,325 --> 00:50:02,325
[SLUGHORN SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY]

563
00:50:03,123 --> 00:50:08,043
Oh, bloody hell.

564
00:50:08,044 --> 00:50:10,212
Slick git.

565
00:50:10,213 --> 00:50:15,213
Honestly, Ronald,
they're only holding hands.

566
00:50:15,719 --> 00:50:17,636
And snogging-

567
00:50:17,637 --> 00:50:20,764
- I'd like to leave.
- What?

568
00:50:20,765 --> 00:50:22,516
You can't be serious.

569
00:50:22,517 --> 00:50:25,060
- That happens to be my sister.
- So?

570
00:50:25,061 --> 00:50:30,061
What if she looked over here and saw you
snogging me? You expect her to leave?

571
00:50:30,275 --> 00:50:32,902
SLUGHORN: Hey, my boy!
HARRY: Hello, sir. Wonderful to see you.

572
00:50:32,903 --> 00:50:35,070
And you, and you.

573
00:50:35,071 --> 00:50:37,031
So, what brings you here?

574
00:50:37,032 --> 00:50:41,911
The Three Broomsticks and I go way back,
further than I care to admit.

575
00:50:41,912 --> 00:50:45,539
I can remember
when it was One Broomstick.

576
00:50:45,540 --> 00:50:49,043
All hands on deck, Granger.
Listen, my boy, in the old days...

577
00:50:49,044 --> 00:50:52,630
I used to throw together
the occasional supper party...

578
00:50:52,631 --> 00:50:55,007
for the select student or two.

579
00:50:55,008 --> 00:51:00,008
- Would you be game?
- I'd consider it an honor, sir.

580
00:51:00,305 --> 00:51:03,307
You would be welcome too, Granger.

581
00:51:03,308 --> 00:51:08,308
- I'd be delighted, sir.
- Splendid. Look for my owl.

582
00:51:08,939 --> 00:51:13,939
Good to see you, Wallenby.

583
00:51:15,820 --> 00:51:19,323
What are you playing at?

584
00:51:19,324 --> 00:51:21,825
Dumbledore's asked me
to get to know him.

585
00:51:21,826 --> 00:51:23,953
- Get to know him?
- I don't know.

586
00:51:23,954 --> 00:51:28,954
It must be important.
If it wasn't, Dumbledore wouldn't ask.

587
00:51:33,296 --> 00:51:38,296
Got a little bit...

588
00:51:46,309 --> 00:51:48,352
LEANNE:
Katie, you don't know what it could be.

589
00:51:48,353 --> 00:51:49,979
RON [WHISPERING]: Harry.
HARRY: What?

590
00:51:49,980 --> 00:51:54,275
RON: Did you hear what she was saying
back at the pub about me and her snogging?

591
00:51:54,276 --> 00:51:59,238
HARRY: As if.

592
00:51:59,239 --> 00:52:02,449
[LEANNE SCREAMS]

593
00:52:02,450 --> 00:52:07,450
I warned her.
I warned her not to touch it.

594
00:52:27,267 --> 00:52:32,267
Don't get any closer.
Get back, all of you.

595
00:52:42,532 --> 00:52:47,532
Do not touch that, except by the wrappings.
Do you understand?

596
00:53:00,842 --> 00:53:03,594
You're sure Katie did not have this
in her possession...

597
00:53:03,595 --> 00:53:06,722
when she entered
the Three Broomsticks?

598
00:53:06,723 --> 00:53:08,474
It's like I Said.

599
00:53:08,475 --> 00:53:13,475
She left to go to the loo, and when
she came back she had the package.

600
00:53:14,648 --> 00:53:18,192
She said it was important
that she deliver it.

601
00:53:18,193 --> 00:53:22,029
- Did she say to whom?
- To Professor Dumbledore.

602
00:53:22,030 --> 00:53:27,030
Very well. Thank you, Leanne.
You may go.

603
00:53:29,412 --> 00:53:34,412
Why is it when something happens
it is always you three?

604
00:53:36,002 --> 00:53:40,964
Believe me, professor, I've been asking
myself the same question for six years.

605
00:53:40,965 --> 00:53:45,965
MCGONAGALL: Oh, Severus.

606
00:53:48,264 --> 00:53:52,059
What do you think?

607
00:53:52,060 --> 00:53:57,022
I think Miss Bell is lucky to be alive.

608
00:53:57,023 --> 00:53:59,441
She was cursed, wasn't she?

609
00:53:59,442 --> 00:54:02,611
I know Katie. Off the pitch,
she wouldn't hurt a fly.

610
00:54:02,612 --> 00:54:06,365
If she was delivering that to Dumbledore,
she wasn't doing it knowingly.

611
00:54:06,366 --> 00:54:09,076
Yes, she was cursed.

612
00:54:09,077 --> 00:54:12,663
It was Malfoy.

613
00:54:12,664 --> 00:54:16,625
That is a very serious accusation, Potter.

614
00:54:16,626 --> 00:54:18,961
Indeed.

615
00:54:18,962 --> 00:54:23,132
- Your evidence?
- I just know.

616
00:54:23,133 --> 00:54:26,343
You just...

617
00:54:26,344 --> 00:54:26,888
know.

618
00:54:30,807 --> 00:54:32,891
You astonish with your gifts, Potter.

619
00:54:32,892 --> 00:54:37,020
Gifts mere mortals
can only dream of possessing.

620
00:54:37,021 --> 00:54:42,021
How grand it must be
to be the Chosen One.

621
00:54:47,824 --> 00:54:52,824
I Suggest you go back to your dormitories.
All of you.

622
00:55:01,838 --> 00:55:06,467
RON: What do you suppose
Dean sees in her? Ginny?

623
00:55:06,468 --> 00:55:08,635
Well, what does she see in him?

624
00:55:08,636 --> 00:55:11,013
Dean? He's brilliant.

625
00:55:11,014 --> 00:55:14,016
You called him a slick git
not five hours ago.

626
00:55:14,017 --> 00:55:17,978
Yeah, well, he was running his hands
all over my sister, wasn't he?

627
00:55:17,979 --> 00:55:22,979
Something snaps, and you've gotta
hate him, you know? On principle.

628
00:55:23,193 --> 00:55:25,944
Isuppose.

629
00:55:25,945 --> 00:55:29,865
- So, what is it he sees in her?
- I don't know.

630
00:55:29,866 --> 00:55:33,035
She's smart, funny.

631
00:55:33,036 --> 00:55:36,872
- Attractive.
- Attractive?

632
00:55:36,873 --> 00:55:41,210
- You know, she's got nice skin.
- Skin?

633
00:55:41,211 --> 00:55:43,212
Dean dates my sister
because of her skin?

634
00:55:43,213 --> 00:55:48,213
Well, no, I mean, I'm just saying
it could be a contributing factor.

635
00:55:51,095 --> 00:55:53,555
Hermione's got nice skin.

636
00:55:53,556 --> 00:55:57,267
Wouldn't you say? As skin goes, I mean.

637
00:55:57,268 --> 00:56:00,896
I've never really thought about it.

638
00:56:00,897 --> 00:56:03,357
But, I suppose, yeah.

639
00:56:03,358 --> 00:56:08,358
Very nice.

640
00:56:09,239 --> 00:56:14,239
- I think I'll be going to sleep now.
- Right. Yeah.

641
00:56:22,460 --> 00:56:26,588
So tell me, Cormac, do you see anything
of your Uncle Tiberius these days?

642
00:56:26,589 --> 00:56:29,258
CORMAC: Yes, sir. In fact,
I'm meant to go hunting with him...

643
00:56:29,259 --> 00:56:31,635
and the Minister for Magic
over the holidays.

644
00:56:31,636 --> 00:56:34,763
Well, be sure to give them both my best.

645
00:56:34,764 --> 00:56:36,932
What about your uncle, Belby?

646
00:56:36,933 --> 00:56:40,561
For those who don't know, Marcus'
uncle invented the Wolfsbane Potion.

647
00:56:40,562 --> 00:56:43,522
- Is he working on anything new?
- Don't know.

648
00:56:43,523 --> 00:56:47,776
Him and Dad don't get on. Probably
because me dad says potions are rubbish.

649
00:56:47,777 --> 00:56:51,238
Says the only potion worth having
is a stiff one at the end of the day.

650
00:56:51,239 --> 00:56:56,239
What about you, Miss Granger? What does
your family do in the Muggle world?

651
00:56:57,120 --> 00:57:02,120
My parents are dentists.

652
00:57:03,501 --> 00:57:04,960
They tend to people's teeth.

653
00:57:04,961 --> 00:57:09,882
Fascinating. And is that considered
a dangerous profession?

654
00:57:09,883 --> 00:57:13,135
HERMIONE: No.

655
00:57:13,136 --> 00:57:17,806
Although, one boy, Robbie Fenwick,
did bite my father once.

656
00:57:17,807 --> 00:57:22,227
He needed 10 stitches.

657
00:57:22,228 --> 00:57:25,314
[DOOR OPENS]

658
00:57:25,315 --> 00:57:30,315
Ah. Miss Weasley. Come in, come in.

659
00:57:31,654 --> 00:57:36,241
[WHISPERS] Look at her eyes.
They've been fighting again, her and Dean.

660
00:57:36,242 --> 00:57:41,242
Sorry. I'm not usually late.

661
00:57:42,749 --> 00:57:47,336
No matter. You're just in time for dessert,
that is, if Belby's left you any.

662
00:57:47,337 --> 00:57:47,837
[LAUGHS]

663
00:57:55,094 --> 00:57:56,345
HARRY: What?

664
00:57:56,346 --> 00:57:56,890
Nothing.

665
00:58:04,312 --> 00:58:09,312
SLUGHORN: Goodbye. Bye-bye.

666
00:58:12,820 --> 00:58:14,738
- Potter.
- I'm sorry, sir.

667
00:58:14,739 --> 00:58:18,700
I was just admiring your hourglass.

668
00:58:18,701 --> 00:58:20,702
SLUGHORN: Oh, yes.

669
00:58:20,703 --> 00:58:23,413
A most intriguing object.

670
00:58:23,414 --> 00:58:27,960
The sand runs in accordance
with the quality of the conversation.

671
00:58:27,961 --> 00:58:31,713
If it is stimulating, the sand runs slowly.

672
00:58:31,714 --> 00:58:33,799
- If it is not...
- I think I'll be going.

673
00:58:33,800 --> 00:58:37,302
Nonsense.
You have nothing to fear, dear boy.

674
00:58:37,303 --> 00:58:39,721
As to some of your classmates...

675
00:58:39,722 --> 00:58:43,308
well, let's just say they're unlikely
to make the shelf.

676
00:58:43,309 --> 00:58:45,394
The shelf, sir?

677
00:58:45,395 --> 00:58:49,189
Anyone who aspires to be anyone
hopes to end up here.

678
00:58:49,190 --> 00:58:54,190
But then again, you already are someone,
aren't you, Harry?

679
00:58:54,612 --> 00:58:58,740
Did Voldemort ever make the shelf, sir?

680
00:58:58,741 --> 00:59:03,741
You knew him, didn't you, sir, Tom Riddle?
You were his teacher.

681
00:59:03,746 --> 00:59:07,416
Mr. Riddle had a number of teachers
whilst here at Hogwarts.

682
00:59:07,417 --> 00:59:12,417
What was he like?

683
00:59:12,714 --> 00:59:15,757
I'm sorry, sir. Forgive me.

684
00:59:15,758 --> 00:59:20,345
He killed my parents.

685
00:59:20,346 --> 00:59:22,014
Of course.

686
00:59:22,015 --> 00:59:27,015
It's only natural
you should want to know more.

687
00:59:27,103 --> 00:59:30,856
But I'm afraid I must disappoint you,
Harry.

688
00:59:30,857 --> 00:59:33,275
When I first met Mr. Riddle,
he was a quiet...

689
00:59:33,276 --> 00:59:37,696
albeit brilliant, boy committed
to becoming a first-rate wizard.

690
00:59:37,697 --> 00:59:40,032
Not unlike others I've known.

691
00:59:40,033 --> 00:59:43,452
Not unlike yourself, in fact.

692
00:59:43,453 --> 00:59:46,079
If the monster existed...

693
00:59:46,080 --> 00:59:51,080
it was buried deep within.

694
01:00:05,641 --> 01:00:08,560
Good luck, eh, Ron.

695
01:00:08,561 --> 01:00:11,188
MAN 1: Nice hat!
MAN 2: Ron, you're a loser.

696
01:00:11,189 --> 01:00:14,441
I'm counting on you, Ron.
I have two Galleons on Gryffindor, yeah?

697
01:00:14,442 --> 01:00:18,987
WOMAN: Looking good, Ron.
MAN 3: Loser!

698
01:00:18,988 --> 01:00:23,988
What's he wearing?

699
01:00:29,123 --> 01:00:32,167
RON: So how was it, then?

700
01:00:32,168 --> 01:00:34,669
- How was what?
- Your dinner party?

701
01:00:34,670 --> 01:00:37,089
HERMIONE:
Pretty boring, actually.

702
01:00:37,090 --> 01:00:42,090
Though I think Harry enjoyed dessert.

703
01:00:42,845 --> 01:00:45,764
Slughorn's having a Christmas do,
you know.

704
01:00:45,765 --> 01:00:47,474
And we're meant to bring someone.

705
01:00:47,475 --> 01:00:51,353
I expect you'll be bringing McLaggen.
He's in the Slug Club, isn't he?

706
01:00:51,354 --> 01:00:56,354
- Actually, I was going to ask you.
RON: Really?

707
01:00:57,026 --> 01:00:59,861
Good luck today, Ron.

708
01:00:59,862 --> 01:01:04,862
I know you'll be brilliant.

709
01:01:05,243 --> 01:01:09,162
I'm resigning. After today's match,
McLaggen can have my spot.

710
01:01:09,163 --> 01:01:10,831
HARRY: Have it your way.

711
01:01:10,832 --> 01:01:13,500
- Juice?
- Sure.

712
01:01:13,501 --> 01:01:16,461
Hello, everyone.

713
01:01:16,462 --> 01:01:18,713
You look dreadful, Ron.

714
01:01:18,714 --> 01:01:23,301
Is that why you put something
in his cup?

715
01:01:23,302 --> 01:01:28,302
Is it a tonic?

716
01:01:28,391 --> 01:01:31,393
HERMIONE: Liquid luck.

717
01:01:31,394 --> 01:01:36,394
Don't drink it, Ron.

718
01:01:40,653 --> 01:01:45,653
- You could be expelled for that.
- I don't know what you're talking about.

719
01:01:46,242 --> 01:01:51,242
Come on, Harry.
We've got a game to win.

720
01:02:11,017 --> 01:02:12,684
[CROWD CHEERING]

721
01:02:12,685 --> 01:02:15,020
Yes!

722
01:02:15,021 --> 01:02:20,021
MAN: Go on, Ron! Do it!

723
01:02:49,639 --> 01:02:51,806
[CROWD CHEERING]

724
01:02:51,807 --> 01:02:54,559
CRQWD <i>[CHANTING]:
Weasley! Weasley! Weasley!</i>

725
01:02:54,560 --> 01:02:56,102
Yes!

726
01:02:56,103 --> 01:03:01,103
<i>Weasley! Weasley! Weasley!</i>

727
01:03:03,361 --> 01:03:05,111
Whoo!

728
01:03:05,112 --> 01:03:09,741
Yes. Whoo!

729
01:03:09,742 --> 01:03:14,742
<i>Weasley! Weasley! Weasley!</i>

730
01:03:19,168 --> 01:03:21,044
You really shouldn't have done it.

731
01:03:21,045 --> 01:03:26,045
I know. I suppose I could've
just used a Confundus Charm.

732
01:03:27,051 --> 01:03:32,051
That was different. That was tryouts.
This was an actual game.

733
01:03:34,475 --> 01:03:37,894
You didn't put it in.

734
01:03:37,895 --> 01:03:42,482
Ron only thought you did.

735
01:03:42,483 --> 01:03:47,483
[CROWD CHEERING]

736
01:04:04,255 --> 01:04:08,758
[HERMIONE SNIFFLING]

737
01:04:08,759 --> 01:04:13,759
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

738
01:04:27,528 --> 01:04:32,528
Charms spell. I'm just practicing.

739
01:04:34,744 --> 01:04:39,744
Well, they're really good.

740
01:04:42,084 --> 01:04:46,921
How does it feel, Harry?

741
01:04:46,922 --> 01:04:51,922
When you see Dean with Ginny?

742
01:04:55,222 --> 01:04:57,766
I know.

743
01:04:57,767 --> 01:05:00,643
I see the way you look at her.

744
01:05:00,644 --> 01:05:04,689
You're my best friend.

745
01:05:04,690 --> 01:05:09,690
[LAVENDER LAUGHING]

746
01:05:11,364 --> 01:05:14,616
Oops.

747
01:05:14,617 --> 01:05:18,620
I think this room's taken.

748
01:05:18,621 --> 01:05:23,416
What's with the birds?

749
01:05:23,417 --> 01:05:23,961
<i>OPPUgno.</i>

750
01:05:53,155 --> 01:05:58,155
It feels like this.

751
01:06:34,572 --> 01:06:37,782
Look, I can't help it
if She's got her knickers in a twist.

752
01:06:37,783 --> 01:06:42,783
What Lav and I have, well,
let's just say, there's no stopping it.

753
01:06:43,038 --> 01:06:44,622
It's chemical.

754
01:06:44,623 --> 01:06:49,127
Will it last? Who knows?
Point is, I'm a free agent.

755
01:06:49,128 --> 01:06:54,128
HERMIONE: He's at perfect liberty to kiss whoever he likes.
I really couldn't care less.

756
01:06:54,717 --> 01:06:58,720
Was I under the impression he and I would
be attending Slughorn's Christmas party?

757
01:06:58,721 --> 01:07:00,388
Yes.

758
01:07:00,389 --> 01:07:04,976
Now, given the circumstances,
I've had to make other arrangements.

759
01:07:04,977 --> 01:07:06,352
Have you?

760
01:07:06,353 --> 01:07:08,521
Yes. Why?

761
01:07:08,522 --> 01:07:12,317
I just thought, seeing as neither of us
can go with who we'd really like to...

762
01:07:12,318 --> 01:07:14,736
we should go together, as friends.

763
01:07:14,737 --> 01:07:16,529
Why didn't I think of that?

764
01:07:16,530 --> 01:07:18,239
Who are you going with?

765
01:07:18,240 --> 01:07:20,200
Um, it's a surprise.

766
01:07:20,201 --> 01:07:25,038
Anyway, it's you we've got to worry about.
You can't just take anyone.

767
01:07:25,039 --> 01:07:28,541
See that girl over there?

768
01:07:28,542 --> 01:07:33,421
That's Romilda Vane. Apparently She's
trying to smuggle you a love potion.

769
01:07:33,422 --> 01:07:35,882
Really?

770
01:07:35,883 --> 01:07:39,511
Hey! She's only interested in you because
she thinks you're the Chosen One.

771
01:07:39,512 --> 01:07:41,387
But I am the Chosen One.

772
01:07:41,388 --> 01:07:46,267
Okay, sorry. Um, kidding.

773
01:07:46,268 --> 01:07:48,520
I'll ask someone I like.

774
01:07:48,521 --> 01:07:53,521
Someone cool.

775
01:07:59,823 --> 01:08:03,034
LUNA:
I've never been to this part of the Castle.

776
01:08:03,035 --> 01:08:06,454
At least not while awake.
I sleepwalk, you see.

777
01:08:06,455 --> 01:08:11,455
That's why I wear shoes to bed.

778
01:08:40,155 --> 01:08:45,155
<i>Harmonia Nectere Passus.</i>

779
01:08:55,671 --> 01:08:59,966
<i>Harmonia Nectere Passus.</i>

780
01:08:59,967 --> 01:09:04,967
<i>Harmonia Nectere Passus.</i>

781
01:09:17,276 --> 01:09:19,611
Drink?

782
01:09:19,612 --> 01:09:21,112
Neville.

783
01:09:21,113 --> 01:09:22,739
I didn't get into the Slug Club.

784
01:09:22,740 --> 01:09:26,034
It's okay, though. He's got Belby
handing out towels in the loo.

785
01:09:26,035 --> 01:09:31,035
- Oh, well, I'm fine, mate. Thanks.
- Okay.

786
01:09:39,256 --> 01:09:42,383
Hermione. What are you doing?
And what happened to you?

787
01:09:42,384 --> 01:09:47,384
I've just escaped.
I mean, left Cormac under the mistletoe.

788
01:09:47,848 --> 01:09:51,059
Cormac? That's who you invited?

789
01:09:51,060 --> 01:09:54,395
I thought it would annoy Ron the most.

790
01:09:54,396 --> 01:09:56,564
SLUGHORN:
Thank you. I'll Catch up with you later.

791
01:09:56,565 --> 01:09:59,734
He's got more tentacles
than a Snarfalump plant.

792
01:09:59,735 --> 01:10:02,070
- Dragon tartare?
- No, I'm fine. Thank you.

793
01:10:02,071 --> 01:10:04,906
Just as well.
They give one horribly bad breath.

794
01:10:04,907 --> 01:10:06,908
On second thoughts...

795
01:10:06,909 --> 01:10:09,243
Might keep Cormac at bay.

796
01:10:09,244 --> 01:10:14,244
Oh, God, here he comes.

797
01:10:14,708 --> 01:10:17,752
I think she just went to powder her nose.

798
01:10:17,753 --> 01:10:20,004
CORMAC:
Slippery little minx, your friend.

799
01:10:20,005 --> 01:10:25,005
Likes to work her mouth too,
doesn't she?

800
01:10:25,761 --> 01:10:28,930
What is this I'm eating, by the way?

801
01:10:28,931 --> 01:10:33,931
Dragon balls.

802
01:10:34,603 --> 01:10:35,147
[VOMITS]

803
01:10:41,777 --> 01:10:45,071
You've just bought yourself
a month's detention, McLaggen.

804
01:10:45,072 --> 01:10:50,072
Not so quick, Potter.

805
01:10:50,494 --> 01:10:53,788
Sir, I really think I should
rejoin the party. My date...

806
01:10:53,789 --> 01:10:57,875
Can surely survive your absence
for another minute or two.

807
01:10:57,876 --> 01:11:00,753
Besides, I only wish
to convey a message.

808
01:11:00,754 --> 01:11:03,172
- A message?
- From Professor Dumbledore.

809
01:11:03,173 --> 01:11:07,009
He asked me to give you his best,
and he hopes you enjoy your holiday.

810
01:11:07,010 --> 01:11:08,720
You see...

811
01:11:08,721 --> 01:11:13,721
he's traveling, and he won't
return until term resumes.

812
01:11:14,435 --> 01:11:19,435
Traveling where?

813
01:11:24,111 --> 01:11:27,113
Take your hands off me, you filthy Squib!

814
01:11:27,114 --> 01:11:28,990
FILCH: Professor Slughorn, sir.

815
01:11:28,991 --> 01:11:33,494
I just discovered this boy
lurking in an upstairs Corridor.

816
01:11:33,495 --> 01:11:35,705
He claims to have been
invited to your party.

817
01:11:35,706 --> 01:11:39,167
Okay, okay. I was gatecrashing. Happy?

818
01:11:39,168 --> 01:11:44,168
I'll escort him out.

819
01:11:45,799 --> 01:11:50,799
Certainly, professor.

820
01:11:53,098 --> 01:11:58,098
All right, everyone, carry on, carry on.

821
01:11:58,437 --> 01:12:03,437
DRACO: Maybe I did hex that Bell girl.
Maybe I didn't. What's it to you?

822
01:12:03,525 --> 01:12:05,777
SNAPE: L swore to protect you.

823
01:12:05,778 --> 01:12:09,280
I made the Unbreakable Vow.

824
01:12:09,281 --> 01:12:11,616
DRACO: I don't need protection.

825
01:12:11,617 --> 01:12:16,617
I was chosen for this.
Out of all others. Me.

826
01:12:16,705 --> 01:12:20,833
- And I won't fail him.
- You're afraid, Draco.

827
01:12:20,834 --> 01:12:24,921
You attempt to conceal it, but it's obvious.
Let me assist you.

828
01:12:24,922 --> 01:12:26,714
DRACO: No!

829
01:12:26,715 --> 01:12:31,715
I was chosen. This is my moment.

830
01:12:42,564 --> 01:12:44,315
RON: "Unbreakable Vow."

831
01:12:44,316 --> 01:12:46,108
You're sure that's what Snape said?

832
01:12:46,109 --> 01:12:48,569
Positive. Why?

833
01:12:48,570 --> 01:12:52,240
Well, it's just you can't break
an Unbreakable Vow.

834
01:12:52,241 --> 01:12:56,077
I'd worked that much out for myself,
funnily enough.

835
01:12:56,078 --> 01:12:58,454
You don't understand.

836
01:12:58,455 --> 01:13:03,455
Oh, bloody hell.

837
01:13:27,317 --> 01:13:30,987
I miss you.

838
01:13:30,988 --> 01:13:32,697
Lovely.

839
01:13:32,698 --> 01:13:36,158
All she wants to do is snog me.
My lips are getting chapped. Look.

840
01:13:36,159 --> 01:13:41,159
I'll take your word for it.

841
01:13:48,463 --> 01:13:53,463
So, what happens to you? What happens
if you break an Unbreakable Vow?

842
01:13:53,969 --> 01:13:54,513
You die.

843
01:14:01,101 --> 01:14:03,394
WOMAN:
Wait, the pudding's still here.

844
01:14:03,395 --> 01:14:06,898
REMUS: Voldemort has chosen
Draco Malfoy for a mission?

845
01:14:06,899 --> 01:14:08,149
I know it sounds mad.

846
01:14:08,150 --> 01:14:11,819
Has it occurred to you Snape was
simply pretending to offer Draco help...

847
01:14:11,820 --> 01:14:14,488
so he could find out
what he was up to?

848
01:14:14,489 --> 01:14:18,034
- That's not what it sounded like.
TONKS: Perhaps Harry's right, Remus.

849
01:14:18,035 --> 01:14:19,827
To make an Unbreakable Vow, it's...

850
01:14:19,828 --> 01:14:23,497
it comes down to whether or not
you trust Dumbledore's judgment.

851
01:14:23,498 --> 01:14:27,752
- Dumbledore trusts Snape, therefore I do.
- Dumbledore can make mistakes.

852
01:14:27,753 --> 01:14:29,086
You're blinded by hatred.

853
01:14:29,087 --> 01:14:32,882
- I'm not.
- Yes, you are.

854
01:14:32,883 --> 01:14:36,052
People are disappearing, Harry, daily.

855
01:14:36,053 --> 01:14:38,179
We place our trust
in a handful of people.

856
01:14:38,180 --> 01:14:43,180
If we start fighting amongst ourselves,
we're doomed.

857
01:15:05,624 --> 01:15:08,834
"099" UP, you.

858
01:15:08,835 --> 01:15:13,835
Don't you trust me?

859
01:15:16,718 --> 01:15:18,719
It's good.

860
01:15:18,720 --> 01:15:23,720
RON:
Yeah, I'll just... Get... Yeah.

861
01:15:28,313 --> 01:15:33,313
- Pie?
- Not for me, no.

862
01:15:43,036 --> 01:15:44,829
ARTHUR:
You'll have to forgive Remus.

863
01:15:44,830 --> 01:15:48,582
It takes its toll, his condition.

864
01:15:48,583 --> 01:15:50,793
HARRY:
Are you all right, Mr. Weasley?

865
01:15:50,794 --> 01:15:53,504
We're being followed, all of us.

866
01:15:53,505 --> 01:15:56,841
Most days,
Molly doesn't leave the house.

867
01:15:56,842 --> 01:16:00,928
It's not been easy.

868
01:16:00,929 --> 01:16:02,513
Did you get my owl?

869
01:16:02,514 --> 01:16:06,100
Yes, I did.

870
01:16:06,101 --> 01:16:09,311
If Dumbledore's traveling,
then that's news to the Ministry...

871
01:16:09,312 --> 01:16:12,481
but perhaps that's the way
Dumbledore wants it.

872
01:16:12,482 --> 01:16:15,609
As for Draco Malfoy...

873
01:16:15,610 --> 01:16:17,403
I know a bit more.

874
01:16:17,404 --> 01:16:20,614
- Go on.
- I sent an agent to Borgin and Burkes.

875
01:16:20,615 --> 01:16:23,117
I think, from what you described...

876
01:16:23,118 --> 01:16:24,952
what you and Ron saw in summer...

877
01:16:24,953 --> 01:16:28,622
the object
that Draco is so interested in...

878
01:16:28,623 --> 01:16:31,000
is a vanishing Cabinet.

879
01:16:31,001 --> 01:16:32,460
A vanishing Cabinet?

880
01:16:32,461 --> 01:16:36,630
They were all the rage
when Voldemort first rose to power.

881
01:16:36,631 --> 01:16:39,759
You can see the appeal.
Should Death Eaters come knocking...

882
01:16:39,760 --> 01:16:44,760
one simply had to slip inside
and disappear for an hour or two.

883
01:16:45,140 --> 01:16:47,058
They can transport you anywhere.

884
01:16:47,059 --> 01:16:50,603
Tricky contraptions though,
very temperamental.

885
01:16:50,604 --> 01:16:53,689
What happened to it?
The one at Borgin and Burkes?

886
01:16:53,690 --> 01:16:55,649
Nothing.

887
01:16:55,650 --> 01:17:00,650
It's still there.

888
01:17:08,455 --> 01:17:10,331
TONKS:
It was delicious, Molly, really.

889
01:17:10,332 --> 01:17:11,832
MOLLY:
Are you sure you won't stay?

890
01:17:11,833 --> 01:17:16,504
No, we should go. The first night
of the cycle's always the worst.

891
01:17:16,505 --> 01:17:17,005
Remus?

892
01:17:26,348 --> 01:17:31,348
Sweetheart.

893
01:17:36,191 --> 01:17:38,109
Has Ron gone to bed?

894
01:17:38,110 --> 01:17:42,738
Um... Not yet. No.

895
01:17:42,739 --> 01:17:43,351
Shoelace.

896
01:17:56,670 --> 01:17:59,964
Merry Christmas, Harry.

897
01:17:59,965 --> 01:18:04,965
Merry Christmas.

898
01:18:18,775 --> 01:18:23,775
- Harm no!
- Remus!

899
01:18:30,912 --> 01:18:31,412
Ginny!

900
01:18:35,500 --> 01:18:40,337
BELLATRIX: <i>Lki/led Sirius Black!
Lki/led Sirius Black!</i>

901
01:18:40,338 --> 01:18:43,674
You coming to get me?

902
01:18:43,675 --> 01:18:48,675
Harry, can you get me?
You coming to get me?

903
01:19:16,750 --> 01:19:17,250
Harry?

904
01:19:35,644 --> 01:19:36,188
<i>Stupefy!</i>

905
01:20:00,168 --> 01:20:05,168
ARTHUR: Harry!

906
01:20:15,433 --> 01:20:15,933
Ginny!

907
01:20:46,214 --> 01:20:46,714
Molly.

908
01:21:10,697 --> 01:21:12,573
HERMIONE:
It's easy for them to get to you.

909
01:21:12,574 --> 01:21:16,869
You're bloody lucky you weren't killed.
You have to realize who you are, Harry.

910
01:21:16,870 --> 01:21:20,372
I know who I am, Hermione, all right?

911
01:21:20,373 --> 01:21:23,250
Sorry.

912
01:21:23,251 --> 01:21:26,754
Lav, come on. Of course I'll wear it.

913
01:21:26,755 --> 01:21:30,924
That's my Won-Won.

914
01:21:30,925 --> 01:21:35,925
Excuse me, I have to go and vomit.

915
01:21:50,987 --> 01:21:53,447
<i>SLUGHORN: I'd like to know
where you get your information.</i>

916
01:21:53,448 --> 01:21:58,448
<i>More knowledgeable
than half the staff, you are.</i>

917
01:22:02,123 --> 01:22:04,124
Sir...

918
01:22:04,125 --> 01:22:07,127
is it true
that Professor Merrythought is retiring?

919
01:22:07,128 --> 01:22:10,172
Now, Tom.
I couldn't tell you if I knew, could I?

920
01:22:10,173 --> 01:22:14,927
By the way, thank you for the pineapple.
You're quite right, it is my favorite.

921
01:22:14,928 --> 01:22:19,056
But how did you know?

922
01:22:19,057 --> 01:22:23,227
Intuition.

923
01:22:23,228 --> 01:22:24,812
[CLOCK CHIMING]

924
01:22:24,813 --> 01:22:26,772
SLUGHORN:
Gracious. Is it that time already?

925
01:22:26,773 --> 01:22:31,773
Off you go, boys, or Professor Dippet
will have us all in detention.

926
01:22:34,489 --> 01:22:39,489
Look sharp, Tom. Don't want to be caught
out of bed after hours.

927
01:22:40,245 --> 01:22:43,664
- Is something on your mind, Tom?
- Yes, sir.

928
01:22:43,665 --> 01:22:47,418
You see, I couldn't think
of anyone else to go to.

929
01:22:47,419 --> 01:22:52,419
The other professors,
well, they're not like you.

930
01:22:52,799 --> 01:22:56,009
They might misunderstand.

931
01:22:56,010 --> 01:22:58,387
Go on.

932
01:22:58,388 --> 01:23:01,223
I was in the library the other night...

933
01:23:01,224 --> 01:23:04,184
in the Restricted Section...

934
01:23:04,185 --> 01:23:08,647
and I read something rather odd
about a bit of rare magic.

935
01:23:08,648 --> 01:23:12,317
And I thought perhaps
you could illuminate me.

936
01:23:12,318 --> 01:23:16,363
It's called, as I understand it...

937
01:23:16,364 --> 01:23:18,031
[RIDDLE SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]

938
01:23:18,032 --> 01:23:19,366
I beg your pardon?

939
01:23:19,367 --> 01:23:23,120
I don't know anything about such things,
and if I did, I wouldn't tell you!

940
01:23:23,121 --> 01:23:28,121
Now, get out of here at once, and don't
let me ever catch you mentioning it again!

941
01:23:30,879 --> 01:23:32,713
DUMBLEDORE: Confused?

942
01:23:32,714 --> 01:23:35,132
I'd be Surprised if you weren't.

943
01:23:35,133 --> 01:23:38,051
Well, I don't understand.
What happened?

944
01:23:38,052 --> 01:23:42,055
This is perhaps the most important
memory I've Collected.

945
01:23:42,056 --> 01:23:44,725
It is also a lie.

946
01:23:44,726 --> 01:23:46,685
This memory has been tampered with...

947
01:23:46,686 --> 01:23:51,686
by the same person whose memory it is,
our old friend, Professor Slughorn.

948
01:23:51,691 --> 01:23:53,859
But why would he tamper
with his own memory?

949
01:23:53,860 --> 01:23:56,904
- I suspect he's ashamed of it.
- Why?

950
01:23:56,905 --> 01:23:59,198
Why, indeed?

951
01:23:59,199 --> 01:24:02,743
I asked you to get to know
Professor Slughorn, and you have done so.

952
01:24:02,744 --> 01:24:06,538
Now I want you to persuade him
to divulge his true memory...

953
01:24:06,539 --> 01:24:08,248
many Way you Can.

954
01:24:08,249 --> 01:24:13,249
I don't know him that well, sir.

955
01:24:14,672 --> 01:24:18,091
This memory is everything.

956
01:24:18,092 --> 01:24:20,594
Without it, We are blind.

957
01:24:20,595 --> 01:24:25,595
Without it, we leave the fate
of our world to Chance.

958
01:24:26,267 --> 01:24:29,311
You have no choice.

959
01:24:29,312 --> 01:24:34,312
You must not fail.

