1200
01:48:07,020 --> 01:48:10,522
king of the arachnids.

1201
01:48:10,523 --> 01:48:14,360
Your body will decay...

1202
01:48:14,361 --> 01:48:17,905
but your spirit lingers on.

1203
01:48:17,906 --> 01:48:22,906
And your human friends find solace
in the loss they have sustained.

1204
01:48:24,829 --> 01:48:29,829
[SLUGHORN & HAGRID SINGING]

1205
01:48:39,719 --> 01:48:43,514
I had him from an egg, you know.
Tiny little thing he was when he hatched.

1206
01:48:43,515 --> 01:48:47,393
No bigger than a Pekinese.
A Pekinese, mind you.

1207
01:48:47,394 --> 01:48:52,394
How sweet. I once had a fish. Francis.
He was very dear to me.

1208
01:48:52,732 --> 01:48:57,732
One afternoon I came downstairs,
and he'd vanished.

1209
01:48:58,071 --> 01:48:59,822
Pooi.

1210
01:48:59,823 --> 01:49:03,200
- That's very odd, isn't it?
- It is, isn't it?

1211
01:49:03,201 --> 01:49:07,079
But that's life, I suppose.

1212
01:49:07,080 --> 01:49:12,080
You go along and then suddenly, poof!

1213
01:49:12,585 --> 01:49:17,585
- Pooi.
- Pooi

1214
01:49:20,927 --> 01:49:25,927
[HAGRID SNORING]

1215
01:49:30,812 --> 01:49:34,940
It was a student who gave me Francis.

1216
01:49:34,941 --> 01:49:39,941
One spring afternoon
I discovered a bowl on my desk...

1217
01:49:40,155 --> 01:49:43,907
with just a few inches
of clear water in it.

1218
01:49:43,908 --> 01:49:48,908
And floating on the surface
was a flower petal.

1219
01:49:48,997 --> 01:49:52,958
As I watched, it sank.

1220
01:49:52,959 --> 01:49:55,961
Just before it reached the bottom...

1221
01:49:55,962 --> 01:49:58,797
it transformed...

1222
01:49:58,798 --> 01:50:02,301
into a wee fish.

1223
01:50:02,302 --> 01:50:05,429
It was beautiful magic.

1224
01:50:05,430 --> 01:50:10,309
Wondrous to behold.

1225
01:50:10,310 --> 01:50:15,310
The flower petal had come from a lily.

1226
01:50:15,440 --> 01:50:18,525
Your mother.

1227
01:50:18,526 --> 01:50:21,987
The day I came downstairs...

1228
01:50:21,988 --> 01:50:25,824
the day the bowl was empty...

1229
01:50:25,825 --> 01:50:30,825
was the day your mother...

1230
01:50:31,998 --> 01:50:36,998
I know why you're here.

1231
01:50:37,003 --> 01:50:40,798
But I can't help you.

1232
01:50:40,799 --> 01:50:45,799
It would ruin me.

1233
01:50:46,221 --> 01:50:49,223
Do you know why I survived, professor?

1234
01:50:49,224 --> 01:50:52,810
The night I got this?

1235
01:50:52,811 --> 01:50:55,354
Because of her.

1236
01:50:55,355 --> 01:50:57,564
Because she sacrificed herself.

1237
01:50:57,565 --> 01:51:00,109
Because she refused to step aside.

1238
01:51:00,110 --> 01:51:03,487
Because her love was more powerful
than Voldemort.

1239
01:51:03,488 --> 01:51:08,033
- Don't say his name.
- I'm not afraid of the name, professor.

1240
01:51:08,034 --> 01:51:11,078
I'm going to tell you something.

1241
01:51:11,079 --> 01:51:15,999
Something others have only guessed at.

1242
01:51:16,000 --> 01:51:18,085
It's true.

1243
01:51:18,086 --> 01:51:20,379
I am the Chosen One.

1244
01:51:20,380 --> 01:51:22,756
Only I can destroy him,
but in order to do so...

1245
01:51:22,757 --> 01:51:26,218
I need to know what Tom Riddle
asked you years ago in your office...

1246
01:51:26,219 --> 01:51:29,304
and I need to know what you told him.

1247
01:51:29,305 --> 01:51:33,350
Be brave, professor.

1248
01:51:33,351 --> 01:51:36,728
Be brave like my mother.

1249
01:51:36,729 --> 01:51:40,524
Otherwise, you disgrace her.

1250
01:51:40,525 --> 01:51:43,819
Otherwise, she died for nothing.

1251
01:51:43,820 --> 01:51:48,820
Ctherwise, the bowl
will remain empty forever.

1252
01:51:59,586 --> 01:52:04,586
Please, don't think badly of me
when you see it.

1253
01:52:04,716 --> 01:52:09,716
You've no idea what he was like,
even then.

1254
01:52:44,756 --> 01:52:47,633
RIDDLE:
I was in the library the other night...

1255
01:52:47,634 --> 01:52:50,677
in the Restricted Section...

1256
01:52:50,678 --> 01:52:55,599
and I read something rather odd
about a bit of rare magic.

1257
01:52:55,600 --> 01:52:59,645
It's called, as I understand it...

1258
01:52:59,646 --> 01:53:02,814
a Horcrux.

1259
01:53:02,815 --> 01:53:05,984
- I beg your pardon?
- Horcrux.

1260
01:53:05,985 --> 01:53:08,820
I came across the term while reading...

1261
01:53:08,821 --> 01:53:11,990
and I didn't fully understand it.

1262
01:53:11,991 --> 01:53:16,662
I'm not sure what you were reading, Tom, but
this is very dark stuff, very dark indeed.

1263
01:53:16,663 --> 01:53:19,331
Which is...

1264
01:53:19,332 --> 01:53:24,002
why I came to you.

1265
01:53:24,003 --> 01:53:29,003
A Horcrux is an object in which a person
has concealed part of their soul.

1266
01:53:29,801 --> 01:53:34,801
But I don't understand
how that works, sir.

1267
01:53:35,014 --> 01:53:39,184
One splits one's soul and hides
part of it in an object.

1268
01:53:39,185 --> 01:53:42,980
By doing so, you're protected, should
you be attacked and your body destroyed.

1269
01:53:42,981 --> 01:53:44,273
Protected?

1270
01:53:44,274 --> 01:53:48,944
That part of your soul
that is hidden lives on.

1271
01:53:48,945 --> 01:53:53,945
In other words, you cannot die.

1272
01:53:58,538 --> 01:54:01,873
And how does one split his soul, sir?

1273
01:54:01,874 --> 01:54:05,877
SLUGHORN: I think you already know
the answer to that, Tom.

1274
01:54:05,878 --> 01:54:07,879
Murder.

1275
01:54:07,880 --> 01:54:09,756
Yes.

1276
01:54:09,757 --> 01:54:14,757
Killing rips the soul apart.
It is a violation against nature.

1277
01:54:15,555 --> 01:54:20,475
RIDDLE: Can you only split the soul once?
For instance, isn't seven...?

1278
01:54:20,476 --> 01:54:22,728
Seven?

1279
01:54:22,729 --> 01:54:27,729
Merlin's beard, Tom. Isn't it bad enough
to consider killing one person?

1280
01:54:28,192 --> 01:54:33,113
To rip the soul into seven pieces...

1281
01:54:33,114 --> 01:54:38,114
This is all hypothetical, isn't it, Tom?
All academic?

1282
01:54:40,913 --> 01:54:45,208
Of course, sir.

1283
01:54:45,209 --> 01:54:50,209
It'll be our little secret.

1284
01:54:56,012 --> 01:55:01,012
HARRY: Sir.

1285
01:55:12,653 --> 01:55:14,946
This is beyond anything I imagined.

1286
01:55:14,947 --> 01:55:17,783
You mean to say he succeeded, sir,
in making a Horcrux?

1287
01:55:17,784 --> 01:55:21,078
Gh, yes, he succeeded, all right.
And not just once.

1288
01:55:21,079 --> 01:55:22,287
What are they exactly?

1289
01:55:22,288 --> 01:55:27,288
Could be anything.
Most commonplace of objects.

1290
01:55:28,795 --> 01:55:31,129
A ring, for example.

1291
01:55:31,130 --> 01:55:33,924
Or a book.

1292
01:55:33,925 --> 01:55:36,802
- Tom Riddle's diary.
- It's a Horcrux, yes.

1293
01:55:36,803 --> 01:55:39,096
Four years ago, when you saved
Ginny's life...

1294
01:55:39,097 --> 01:55:41,556
in the Chamber of Secrets,
you brought me this.

1295
01:55:41,557 --> 01:55:43,642
I knew this was
a different kind of magic.

1296
01:55:43,643 --> 01:55:48,643
Very dark, very powerful. But until tonight
I had no idea just how powerful.

1297
01:55:48,815 --> 01:55:51,191
- The ring?
- Belonged to Voldemort's mother.

1298
01:55:51,192 --> 01:55:56,113
Difficult to find.
Even more difficult to destroy.

1299
01:55:56,114 --> 01:56:00,158
But if you could find them all,
if you did destroy each Horcrux...

1300
01:56:00,159 --> 01:56:01,493
One destroys Voldemort.

1301
01:56:01,494 --> 01:56:04,579
But how would you find them?
They could be hidden anywhere.

1302
01:56:04,580 --> 01:56:09,580
True. But magic, especially dark magic...

1303
01:56:21,806 --> 01:56:26,806
leaves traces.

1304
01:56:31,482 --> 01:56:33,733
It's where you've been going,
isn't it, sir?

1305
01:56:33,734 --> 01:56:36,862
- When you leave the school?
- Yes.

1306
01:56:36,863 --> 01:56:40,115
And I think perhaps
I may have found another.

1307
01:56:40,116 --> 01:56:45,116
But this time,
I cannot hope to destroy it alone.

1308
01:56:45,746 --> 01:56:50,746
Once again,
I must ask too much of you, Harry.

1309
01:56:54,380 --> 01:56:56,840
SNAPE: Have you ever considered
that you ask too much...

1310
01:56:56,841 --> 01:56:59,634
that you take too much for granted?

1311
01:56:59,635 --> 01:57:04,635
Has it ever crossed your brilliant mind
that I don't want to do this anymore?

1312
01:57:04,849 --> 01:57:07,851
Whether it has or hasn't is irrelevant.

1313
01:57:07,852 --> 01:57:12,852
I will not negotiate with you, Severus.
You agreed. Nothing more to discuss.

1314
01:57:32,043 --> 01:57:36,254
Oh, Harry.

1315
01:57:36,255 --> 01:57:41,255
You need a shave, my friend.

1316
01:57:41,385 --> 01:57:45,764
You know, at times,
I forget how much you've grown.

1317
01:57:45,765 --> 01:57:50,765
At times, I still see the small boy
from the cupboard.

1318
01:57:51,270 --> 01:57:54,105
Forgive my mawkishness, Harry.

1319
01:57:54,106 --> 01:57:55,774
I'm an old man.

1320
01:57:55,775 --> 01:57:58,902
You still look the same to me, sir.

1321
01:57:58,903 --> 01:58:02,072
Just like your mother,
you're unfailingly kind.

1322
01:58:02,073 --> 01:58:07,073
A trait people never fail to undervalue,
I'm afraid.

1323
01:58:08,037 --> 01:58:12,707
The place to which we journey tonight
is extremely dangerous.

1324
01:58:12,708 --> 01:58:16,378
I promised you could accompany me,
and I stand by that promise.

1325
01:58:16,379 --> 01:58:18,380
But there is one condition:

1326
01:58:18,381 --> 01:58:22,467
You must obey every command
I give you, without question.

1327
01:58:22,468 --> 01:58:24,261
Yes, sir.

1328
01:58:24,262 --> 01:58:26,972
You do understand what I'm saying?

1329
01:58:26,973 --> 01:58:29,641
Should I tell you to hide, you hide.

1330
01:58:29,642 --> 01:58:32,143
Should I tell you to run, you run.

1331
01:58:32,144 --> 01:58:37,144
Should I tell you to abandon me
and save yourself, you must do so.

1332
01:58:41,320 --> 01:58:44,531
Your word, Harry.

1333
01:58:44,532 --> 01:58:46,825
My word.

1334
01:58:46,826 --> 01:58:49,911
Take my arm.

1335
01:58:49,912 --> 01:58:52,998
Sir, I thought you couldn't
Apparate within Hogwarts.

1336
01:58:52,999 --> 01:58:57,999
Well, being me has its privileges.

1337
01:59:43,716 --> 01:59:46,134
DUMBLEDORE: This is the place.

1338
01:59:46,135 --> 01:59:48,637
Oh, yes.

1339
01:59:48,638 --> 01:59:53,638
This place has known magic.

1340
01:59:59,231 --> 02:00:00,940
- Sir!
- Ln order to gain passage...

1341
02:00:00,941 --> 02:00:02,525
payment must be made.

1342
02:00:02,526 --> 02:00:07,526
Payment intended
to weaken any intruder.

1343
02:00:07,740 --> 02:00:10,033
- You should've let me, sir.
- No, Harry.

1344
02:00:10,034 --> 02:00:15,034
Your blood's much more precious
than mine.

1345
02:00:34,642 --> 02:00:39,437
Voldemort will not have made it easy
to discover his hiding place.

1346
02:00:39,438 --> 02:00:44,438
He will have put certain defenses
in position.

1347
02:00:45,361 --> 02:00:45,905
Careful.

1348
02:01:10,302 --> 02:01:12,929
There it is.

1349
02:01:12,930 --> 02:01:17,930
The only question is,
how do we get there?

1350
02:01:37,830 --> 02:01:42,830
If you would, Harry.

1351
02:02:26,962 --> 02:02:30,006
Do you think the Horcrux is in there, sir?

1352
02:02:30,007 --> 02:02:30,551
Oh, yes.

1353
02:02:42,478 --> 02:02:44,229
It has to be drunk.

1354
02:02:44,230 --> 02:02:47,899
All of it has to be drunk.

1355
02:02:47,900 --> 02:02:51,402
You remember the conditions on which
I brought you with me?

1356
02:02:51,403 --> 02:02:54,239
This potion might paralyze me.

1357
02:02:54,240 --> 02:02:56,699
Might make me forget why I'm here.

1358
02:02:56,700 --> 02:03:00,245
Might cause me so much pain
that I beg for relief.

1359
02:03:00,246 --> 02:03:02,330
You are not to indulge these requests.

1360
02:03:02,331 --> 02:03:06,042
It's your job, Harry, to make sure
I keep drinking this potion.

1361
02:03:06,043 --> 02:03:08,962
Even if you have to force it
down my throat.

1362
02:03:08,963 --> 02:03:11,256
- Understood?
- Why can't I drink it, sir?

1363
02:03:11,257 --> 02:03:16,257
Because I am much older, much cleverer,
and much less valuable.

1364
02:03:20,599 --> 02:03:25,599
Your good health, Harry.

1365
02:03:38,826 --> 02:03:42,245
Professor.

1366
02:03:42,246 --> 02:03:43,621
Professor!

1367
02:03:43,622 --> 02:03:48,622
[DUMBLEDORE GROANING]

1368
02:03:50,129 --> 02:03:51,796
Harry.

1369
02:03:51,797 --> 02:03:55,592
HARRY:
Professor, can you hear me?

1370
02:03:55,593 --> 02:04:00,593
Professor.

1371
02:04:12,192 --> 02:04:13,484
No. Doni.

1372
02:04:13,485 --> 02:04:18,485
You have to keep drinking,
like you said. Remember?

1373
02:04:25,080 --> 02:04:27,123
DUMBLEDORE: Stop.
- It will stop. It will stop...

1374
02:04:27,124 --> 02:04:31,711
- ...but only if you keep drinking.
- Please, don't make me.

1375
02:04:31,712 --> 02:04:34,005
- I'm sorry, sir.
- Please.

1376
02:04:34,006 --> 02:04:38,217
- Kill me. Kill me!
- No!

1377
02:04:38,218 --> 02:04:40,970
DUMBLEDORE: It's my fault.

1378
02:04:40,971 --> 02:04:44,015
It's all my fault.

1379
02:04:44,016 --> 02:04:45,808
It's my fault.

1380
02:04:45,809 --> 02:04:49,854
HARRY: Just one more, sir.
One more, and then I promise...

1381
02:04:49,855 --> 02:04:52,357
I promise I'll do what you say.

1382
02:04:52,358 --> 02:04:55,234
- I promise.
- No.

1383
02:04:55,235 --> 02:04:55,735
Please.

1384
02:05:20,761 --> 02:05:21,261
Harry.

1385
02:05:29,353 --> 02:05:31,396
Water.

1386
02:05:31,397 --> 02:05:32,689
Water.

1387
02:05:32,690 --> 02:05:33,190
Water.

1388
02:05:40,990 --> 02:05:42,949
You did it, sir.

1389
02:05:42,950 --> 02:05:46,411
Look.

1390
02:05:46,412 --> 02:05:49,038
Harry.

1391
02:05:49,039 --> 02:05:52,125
Water.

1392
02:05:52,126 --> 02:05:54,002
<i>Aguamenti.</i>

1393
02:05:54,003 --> 02:05:59,003
DUMBLEDORE: Water.

1394
02:06:31,623 --> 02:06:32,123
<i>Lumos.</i>

1395
02:06:54,772 --> 02:06:59,772
[SPLASHING]

1396
02:07:01,445 --> 02:07:06,445
<i>Lumos Maxima!</i>

1397
02:07:12,831 --> 02:07:17,831
DUMBLEDORE: Harry.

1398
02:07:18,712 --> 02:07:20,004
<i>Sectumsempra!</i>

1399
02:07:20,005 --> 02:07:22,131
Harry.

1400
02:07:22,132 --> 02:07:27,132
Stupefyl DUMBLEDORE: Harry.

1401
02:08:22,943 --> 02:08:27,943
DUMBLEDORE: Harry.

1402
02:08:28,240 --> 02:08:33,240
<i>Partis Temporus!</i>

1403
02:09:01,857 --> 02:09:06,857
[THUNDER CRASHING]

1404
02:09:13,118 --> 02:09:18,118
Go to your houses. No dawdling.

1405
02:09:32,888 --> 02:09:33,500
[TICKING]

1406
02:09:57,079 --> 02:10:02,079
We need to get you to the hospital
wing, sir, to Madam Pomfrey.

1407
02:10:03,210 --> 02:10:05,628
No.

1408
02:10:05,629 --> 02:10:08,464
Severus. Severus is who I need.

1409
02:10:08,465 --> 02:10:12,176
Wake him. Tell him what happened.

1410
02:10:12,177 --> 02:10:14,470
Speak to no one else.

1411
02:10:14,471 --> 02:10:18,557
Severus, Harry.

1412
02:10:18,558 --> 02:10:21,978
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

1413
02:10:21,979 --> 02:10:25,856
Hide yourself below, Harry.

1414
02:10:25,857 --> 02:10:29,026
Don't speak or be seen by anybody
without my permission.

1415
02:10:29,027 --> 02:10:33,614
Whatever happens,
it's imperative you stay below.

1416
02:10:33,615 --> 02:10:35,449
Harry, do as I say.

1417
02:10:35,450 --> 02:10:38,911
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

1418
02:10:38,912 --> 02:10:41,956
Trust me.

1419
02:10:41,957 --> 02:10:42,569
Trust me.

1420
02:11:03,979 --> 02:11:06,689
Good evening, Draco.

1421
02:11:06,690 --> 02:11:10,401
What brings you here
on this fine spring evening?

1422
02:11:10,402 --> 02:11:12,320
Who else is here? I heard you talking.

1423
02:11:12,321 --> 02:11:17,321
DUMBLEDORE: I often talk aloud to myself.
I find it extraordinarily useful.

1424
02:11:18,535 --> 02:11:23,535
Have you been whispering
to yourself, Draco?

1425
02:11:23,874 --> 02:11:26,000
Draco...

1426
02:11:26,001 --> 02:11:29,128
- ...you are no assassin.
- How do you know what I am?

1427
02:11:29,129 --> 02:11:31,088
I've done things that would shock you.

1428
02:11:31,089 --> 02:11:35,384
Like cursing Katie Bell and hoping that in
return she'd bear a cursed necklace to me?

1429
02:11:35,385 --> 02:11:38,179
Replacing a bottle of mead
with one laced with poison?

1430
02:11:38,180 --> 02:11:39,930
Forgive me, Draco.

1431
02:11:39,931 --> 02:11:42,600
I cannot help feeling these actions
are so weak...

1432
02:11:42,601 --> 02:11:45,144
your heart can't really
have been in them.

1433
02:11:45,145 --> 02:11:50,145
He trusts me. I was chosen.

1434
02:11:52,152 --> 02:11:54,111
DUMBLEDORE:
Then I shall make it easy for you.

1435
02:11:54,112 --> 02:11:59,112
<i>Expe/liarmus!</i>

1436
02:11:59,117 --> 02:12:01,619
DUMBLEDORE:
Very good. Very good.

1437
02:12:01,620 --> 02:12:03,204
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

1438
02:12:03,205 --> 02:12:05,748
You're not alone.

1439
02:12:05,749 --> 02:12:08,834
There are others.

1440
02:12:08,835 --> 02:12:11,545
How?

1441
02:12:11,546 --> 02:12:14,965
The vanishing Cabinet
in the Room of Requirement.

1442
02:12:14,966 --> 02:12:17,510
- I've been mending it.
DUMBLEDORE: Let me guess.

1443
02:12:17,511 --> 02:12:20,638
It has a sister. A twin.

1444
02:12:20,639 --> 02:12:23,015
In Borgin and Burkes.
They form a passage.

1445
02:12:23,016 --> 02:12:25,476
DUMBLEDORE: Ingenious.

1446
02:12:25,477 --> 02:12:26,894
Draco...

1447
02:12:26,895 --> 02:12:31,895
years ago, I knew a boy
who made all the wrong Choices.

1448
02:12:33,902 --> 02:12:37,613
- Please let me help you.
- I don't want your help!

1449
02:12:37,614 --> 02:12:42,326
Don't you understand? I have to do this.

1450
02:12:42,327 --> 02:12:44,620
I have to kill you.

1451
02:12:44,621 --> 02:12:49,621
Or he's gonna kill me.

1452
02:12:56,174 --> 02:13:01,174
Well, look what we have here.

1453
02:13:01,680 --> 02:13:06,680
Well done, Draco.

1454
02:13:07,519 --> 02:13:10,396
DUMBLEDORE:
Good evening, Bellatrix.

1455
02:13:10,397 --> 02:13:12,731
I think introductions
are in order, don't you?

1456
02:13:12,732 --> 02:13:17,732
BELLATRIX: Love to, Albus, but I'm afraid
we're all on a bit of a tight schedule.

1457
02:13:18,488 --> 02:13:21,157
Do it.

1458
02:13:21,158 --> 02:13:25,703
GREYBACK: He doesn't have the stomach,
just like his father.

1459
02:13:25,704 --> 02:13:27,371
Let me finish him in my own way.

1460
02:13:27,372 --> 02:13:31,167
BELLATRIX: No! The Dark Lord was Clear,
the boy is to do it.

1461
02:13:31,168 --> 02:13:34,753
This is your moment. Do it.

1462
02:13:34,754 --> 02:13:36,922
Go on, Draco.

1463
02:13:36,923 --> 02:13:40,342
Now!

1464
02:13:40,343 --> 02:13:45,343
SNAPE: No.

1465
02:13:53,565 --> 02:13:58,565
DUMBLEDORE: Severus.

1466
02:14:04,117 --> 02:14:06,577
Please.

1467
02:14:06,578 --> 02:14:11,578
<i>Avada Kedavra.</i>

1468
02:14:23,929 --> 02:14:24,429
[YELLS]

1469
02:14:50,872 --> 02:14:51,372
Yeah!

1470
02:15:12,310 --> 02:15:15,938
BELLATRIX: Hagrid! Hello?

1471
02:15:15,939 --> 02:15:20,939
HARRY: Snape! He trusted you!

1472
02:15:22,946 --> 02:15:24,321
[SQUEALING]

1473
02:15:24,322 --> 02:15:26,615
SNAPE: Go on.

1474
02:15:26,616 --> 02:15:28,492
<i>Incarcerous.</i>

1475
02:15:28,493 --> 02:15:32,788
Fight back! You coward, fight back!

1476
02:15:32,789 --> 02:15:37,789
SNAPE:
No! He belongs to the Dark Lord.

1477
02:15:56,146 --> 02:16:01,146
<i>Sectumsempra!</i>

1478
02:16:05,989 --> 02:16:10,989
You dare use my own spells
against me, Potter?

1479
02:16:11,995 --> 02:16:13,871
Yes.

1480
02:16:13,872 --> 02:16:18,872
I'm the Half-Blood Prince.

1481
02:18:52,155 --> 02:18:52,767
[SOBBING]

1482
02:20:06,104 --> 02:20:08,272
MCGONAGALL: Potter...

1483
02:20:08,273 --> 02:20:12,192
in light of what has happened...

1484
02:20:12,193 --> 02:20:17,193
if you should have the need
to talk to someone...

1485
02:20:17,448 --> 02:20:22,448
You should know,
Professor Dumbledore...

1486
02:20:23,288 --> 02:20:28,288
you meant a great deal to him.

1487
02:20:44,017 --> 02:20:46,351
HERMIONE:
Do you think he would've done it?

1488
02:20:46,352 --> 02:20:49,313
Draco?

1489
02:20:49,314 --> 02:20:51,815
HARRY: No.

1490
02:20:51,816 --> 02:20:54,902
No, he was lowering his wand.

1491
02:20:54,903 --> 02:20:57,487
In the end, it was Snape.

1492
02:20:57,488 --> 02:21:00,115
It was always Snape.

1493
02:21:00,116 --> 02:21:05,116
And I did nothing.

1494
02:21:09,000 --> 02:21:12,002
It's fake.

1495
02:21:12,003 --> 02:21:12,547
Open it.

1496
02:21:24,349 --> 02:21:28,518
"To the Dark Lord. I know I will be dead
long before you read this..."

1497
02:21:28,519 --> 02:21:33,190
but I want you to know that it was I
who discovered your secret.

1498
02:21:33,191 --> 02:21:37,235
I have stolen the real Horcrux and intend
to destroy it as soon as I can.

1499
02:21:37,236 --> 02:21:40,447
I face death in the hope that
when you meet your match...

1500
02:21:40,448 --> 02:21:43,992
you will be mortal once more.

1501
02:21:43,993 --> 02:21:46,912
"R.A.B."

1502
02:21:46,913 --> 02:21:48,747
R.A.B.

1503
02:21:48,748 --> 02:21:52,042
Don't know.

1504
02:21:52,043 --> 02:21:55,671
But whoever they are,
they have the real Horcrux.

1505
02:21:55,672 --> 02:21:58,548
Which means it was all a waste.

1506
02:21:58,549 --> 02:22:03,549
All of it.

1507
02:22:06,265 --> 02:22:08,850
Ron's okay with it, you know.

1508
02:22:08,851 --> 02:22:10,978
You and Ginny.

1509
02:22:10,979 --> 02:22:15,979
But if I were you, when he's around,
I'd keep the snogging to a minimum.

1510
02:22:16,025 --> 02:22:19,194
HARRY:
I'm not coming back, Hermione.

1511
02:22:19,195 --> 02:22:22,072
I've got to finish
whatever Dumbledore started.

1512
02:22:22,073 --> 02:22:25,075
And I don't know where that'll lead me...

1513
02:22:25,076 --> 02:22:30,038
but I'll let you and Ron know
where I am when I can.

1514
02:22:30,039 --> 02:22:32,833
I've always admired your Courage, Harry.

1515
02:22:32,834 --> 02:22:37,834
But sometimes, you can be really thick.

1516
02:22:38,548 --> 02:22:40,966
You don't really think
you're going to be able...

1517
02:22:40,967 --> 02:22:45,967
to find all those Horcruxes
by yourself, do you?

1518
02:22:47,598 --> 02:22:52,598
You need us, Harry.

1519
02:23:05,074 --> 02:23:10,074
HARRY: I never realized
how beautiful this place was.

1520
02:23:10,580 --> 02:23:15,580
[BIRD CRIES]

